**Word Counter Program in C++**
================================

### Program Description

This program reads a text file line by line, counts the occurrences of a specific word, and displays the result.

### Code
```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
#include <sstream>
#include <string>
#include <map>

// Function to count word occurrences in a file
int countWordOccurrences(const std::string& filename, const std::string& word) {
    std::ifstream file(filename);
    if (!file.is_open()) {
        std::cerr << "Error opening file: " << filename << std::endl;
        return -1;
    }

    int count = 0;
    std::string line, wordLower;
    while (std::getline(file, line)) {
        std::istringstream iss(line);
        while (iss >> wordLower) {
            for (char& c : wordLower) {
                c = std::tolower(c); // Convert to lowercase for case-insensitive comparison
            }
            if (wordLower == word) {
                count++;
            }
        }
    }
    file.close();
    return count;
}

int main() {
    std::string filename, word;
    std::cout << "Enter the filename: ";
    std::cin >> filename;
    std::cout << "Enter the word to count: ";
    std::cin >> word;

    int occurrences = countWordOccurrences(filename, word);
    if (occurrences!= -1) {
        std::cout << "The word '" << word << "' occurs " << occurrences << " times in the file." << std::endl;
    }
    return 0;
}
```

### Usage

1. Compile the program: `g++ word_counter.cpp -o word_counter`
2. Run the program: `./word_counter`
3. Enter the filename and the word to count when prompted.
4. The program will display the number of occurrences of the word

